            </table>
            <p>The funding amount for each type of livestock is different because some tests cost more to do.</p>
            <p>The funding will contribute to the cost of testing as well as your time and the vet's time.</p>
            <h2 id="before-the-review">How it works</h2>
            <p>There are two routes into the service. If you have an existing agreement and have had an annual health and welfare review and claimed your funding in the last 10 months, you should apply for a follow-up and start from step 4 in the list below.</p>
            <p>If you have had an annual health and welfare review but have not yet claimed, you should first claim your funding, then apply for a follow-up.</p>
            <p>You’ll only be eligible for funding if the vet carries out sampling after your agreement start date. This must be during or after the first time the vet visits your farm and before you claim.</p>
            <p>If you are new to the service, or not had an annual health and welfare review within the last 10 months, start from step one.</p>
            <ol class="steps">
              <li>
                <p>Apply and accept your agreement</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>Arrange a review and agree payment with the vet</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>Claim your funding online</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p> No more than 10 months later, organise a follow-up visit for the vet to test for endemic diseases on the same livestock type as your review</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>Ask your vet to take samples for the endemic disease follow-up testing</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>Arrange for your vet to carry out a biosecurity assessment</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>Submit your results when you claim your funding</p>
              </li>
            </ol>
            <p>You must agree with the vet what they’ll focus on. Ask them to read the <a href="#">[vet guidance].</a>
            </p>
